Michael H. Thaman: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 6:44 PM ET
Building Products

Company Overview of Owens Corning



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Michael H. Thaman  Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer and President, Owens CorningAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships53$8,946,268As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Michael H. Thaman, also known as Mike, serves as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Owens Corning Canada LP. Mr. Thaman has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Owens Corning since December 6, 2007. Mr. Thaman serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Owens Corning Fabwel, LLC. joined Owens in 1992 and served as its Chief Financial Officer from 2000 to September 2007. Previously, he served as President of the Exterior Systems Business ... beginning in 1999 and President of the Engineered Pipe Systems Business beginning January 1997 to December 1998. Mr. Thaman served as Vice President at Mercer Management Consulting. He has been the Chairman of the Board of Owens Corning since April 2002 and has been its Director since January 2002. He serves as the Chairman of Owens Corning Fabwel, LLC. He serves as Chairman of the Policy Advisory Board of the Harvard Joint Center for Housing Studies of Harvard University. He has been a Director of The Sherwin-Williams Company since April 2017. He serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Kohler Company. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Board of Marble Harbor Investment Counsel, LLC. He served as Director of Florida Power & Light Company. He served as Director of AGY Holding Corp., since April 2000. He served as Independent Director of NextEra Energy, Inc., since July 2003 to May 22, 2014 and served as its Lead Independent Director. He is a member of Business Roundtable, where he previously chaired the Energy Efficiency Task Force. Mr. Thaman earned a Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from Princeton University in 1986.Read Full Background




